{
  "threads": [
    {
      "id": "thread_pmc1_alignment_slot",
      "subject": "MOB Launch – early-week alignment slot",
      "messages": [
        {
          "id": "email_pmc1_1@company.com",
          "from": "alex.smith@company.com",
          "to": [
            "jordan.johnson@company.com",
            "sam.williams@company.com",
            "taylor.brown@company.com"
          ],
          "subject": "MOB Launch – early-week alignment slot",
          "body": "Hi all,\n\nAhead of the Mobile App Launch \"Planning\" milestone on 11/10 and the \"Development\" kickoff on 11/20, I’d like us to get in the same (virtual) room to align on scope, risks, and ownership.\n\nLooking at everyone’s rough availability, the cleanest overlap seems to be **Tuesday 11/11 from 2–3pm ET**. I’ve penciled that in on my calendar as a focus block for MOB Launch, but I’d like to turn that into a dedicated sync with the four of us (R&D + Eng leads).\n\nCan you confirm if **Tues 11/11, 2–3pm ET** works for you? If not, please reply with conflicts and I’ll find a nearby alternative.\n\nTentative agenda:\n- Quick status on MOB-100 / MOB-101\n- Finalize MVP vs. stretch goals\n- Dependencies and ownership split (R&D vs Eng)\n- Risks / open questions before the Planning milestone\n\nThanks,\nAlex\n",
          "date": "2025-11-03T14:02:00-05:00"
        },
        {
          "id": "email_pmc1_2@company.com",
          "from": "sam.williams@company.com",
          "to": [
            "alex.smith@company.com"
          ],
          "subject": "Re: MOB Launch – early-week alignment slot",
          "body": "Hi Alex,\n\nWorks for me – Tues 11/11 2–3pm ET is good. I’ve got another review right before, so if anything shifts earlier than 2pm I may need to drop for the first few minutes, but the proposed time is clear on my side.\n\nSam\n",
          "date": "2025-11-03T14:10:00-05:00"
        },
        {
          "id": "email_pmc1_3@company.com",
          "from": "taylor.brown@company.com",
          "to": [
            "alex.smith@company.com"
          ],
          "subject": "Re: MOB Launch – early-week alignment slot",
          "body": "Hi Alex,\n\n2–3pm ET on 11/11 works on my side as well. I’ve got some open questions on the ownership split for the onboarding flows, so this will be a good time to sort those out.\n\nTaylor\n",
          "date": "2025-11-03T14:16:00-05:00"
        },
        {
          "id": "email_pmc1_4@company.com",
          "from": "jordan.johnson@company.com",
          "to": [
            "alex.smith@company.com"
          ],
          "subject": "Re: MOB Launch – early-week alignment slot",
          "body": "Alex,\n\nConfirmed – I’m free 2–3pm ET on Tues 11/11. I’ve been keeping that general window lighter for MOB work anyway, so turning it into a planning sync works well.\n\nJordan\n",
          "date": "2025-11-03T14:24:00-05:00"
        },
        {
          "id": "email_pmc1_5@company.com",
          "from": "alex.smith@company.com",
          "to": [
            "jordan.johnson@company.com",
            "sam.williams@company.com",
            "taylor.brown@company.com"
          ],
          "subject": "Re: MOB Launch – early-week alignment slot",
          "body": "Thanks all,\n\nSince it sounds like **Tues 11/11, 2–3pm ET** works across the board, I’ll convert my existing MOB Launch focus hold into a proper calendar invite for the four of us. It’ll show up as “Mobile App Launch – cross-team planning sync” with a Meet link.\n\nNo need to reply unless something changes on your side.\n\nAlex\n",
          "date": "2025-11-03T14:32:00-05:00"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "thread_wr_draft_internal",
      "subject": "Draft – MOB Weekly Update (do not send)",
      "messages": [
        {
          "id": "email_wr_draft_1@company.com",
          "from": "alex.smith@company.com",
          "to": [
            "alex.smith@company.com"
          ],
          "subject": "Draft – MOB Weekly Update (do not send)",
          "body": "MOB – Weekly Update (Draft)\n\nKey wins this week:\n- App performance has improved noticeably; cold start times and key API calls are trending in the right direction.\n- We’re seeing solid week-over-week user growth as we ramp up the beta cohort.\n\nStill need to tighten the wording and add exact percentages before sending to the broader list.\n\nAlex\n",
          "date": "2025-11-07T12:05:00-05:00"
        },
        {
          "id": "email_wr_draft_2@company.com",
          "from": "alex.smith@company.com",
          "to": [
            "sam.williams@company.com"
          ],
          "subject": "Fwd: Draft – MOB Weekly Update (do not send)",
          "body": "Hi Sam,\n\nForwarding you my rough draft for the MOB weekly update (below). Before I finalize and send this broadly, can you double-check that my qualitative read on performance and user growth is directionally accurate? I’m planning to translate the dashboard exports into something like “~15% performance improvement” and “~10% user growth” but want to make sure that won’t be misleading.\n\nIf anything feels off or over/understated, let me know and I’ll tweak the language.\n\nThanks,\nAlex\n\n--- Forwarded message ---\nFrom: Alex Smith <alex.smith@company.com>\nDate: Fri, Nov 7, 2025 at 12:05 PM\nSubject: Draft – MOB Weekly Update (do not send)\nTo: Alex Smith <alex.smith@company.com>\n\nMOB – Weekly Update (Draft)\n\nKey wins this week:\n- App performance has improved noticeably; cold start times and key API calls are trending in the right direction.\n- We’re seeing solid week-over-week user growth as we ramp up the beta cohort.\n\nStill need to tighten the wording and add exact percentages before sending to the broader list.\n\nAlex\n",
          "date": "2025-11-07T12:22:00-05:00"
        },
        {
          "id": "email_wr_draft_3@company.com",
          "from": "sam.williams@company.com",
          "to": [
            "alex.smith@company.com"
          ],
          "subject": "Re: Fwd: Draft – MOB Weekly Update (do not send)",
          "body": "Hey Alex,\n\nI took a quick look. Based on the latest dashboard export, we’re seeing roughly a 15% improvement on app startup and similar gains on the p95 for the core APIs. Weekly active users and new signups are both up by about 10% week-over-week.\n\nSo framing it as “roughly 15% performance improvement” and “about 10% user growth” is accurate enough for a stakeholder note.\n\nSam\n",
          "date": "2025-11-07T12:38:00-05:00"
        },
        {
          "id": "email_wr_draft_4@company.com",
          "from": "alex.smith@company.com",
          "to": [
            "alex.smith@company.com"
          ],
          "subject": "Re: Draft – MOB Weekly Update (do not send)",
          "body": "Note to self:\n\nPer Sam’s confirmation, use:\n- “roughly a 15% improvement” for key performance metrics (startup + critical API paths)\n- “about 10% week-over-week growth” for both active users and new signups\n\nIncorporate these into the final stakeholder-facing update and the Confluence status log.\n\nAlex\n",
          "date": "2025-11-07T12:45:00-05:00"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "thread_wr_final_update",
      "subject": "MOB – Weekly Update (week of Nov 7)",
      "messages": [
        {
          "id": "email_wr_final_1@company.com",
          "from": "alex.smith@company.com",
          "to": [
            "sam.williams@company.com",
            "jordan.johnson@company.com",
            "taylor.brown@company.com"
          ],
          "subject": "MOB – Weekly Update (week of Nov 7)",
          "body": "Hi all,\n\nHere’s the Mobile App Launch update for the week of Nov 7.\n\nHighlights\n- **Performance**: We saw roughly a **15% improvement** in key app performance metrics week-over-week (e.g., app startup and critical API paths), which is already noticeable in beta usage.\n- **User growth**: Our beta cohort continued to ramp, with about **10% week-over-week growth** in both active users and new signups.\n- **Stability**: Error rates remained stable despite the increased traffic.\n\nWhat’s next\n- Keep iterating on performance for the flows tied to MOB-101 (core feature).\n- Use next Tuesday’s cross-team planning sync (2–3pm ET) to finalize MVP vs stretch scope for launch and clarify ownership across R&D and Engineering.\n\nThanks,\nAlex\n",
          "date": "2025-11-07T16:30:00-05:00"
        },
        {
          "id": "email_wr_final_2@company.com",
          "from": "taylor.brown@company.com",
          "to": [
            "alex.smith@company.com"
          ],
          "subject": "Re: MOB – Weekly Update (week of Nov 7)",
          "body": "Alex,\n\nNice progress, thanks for the clear summary. The way you framed the performance and growth improvements lines up with what my team has been seeing in the beta dashboards.\n\nLooking forward to Tuesday’s planning sync to lock in the MVP scope.\n\nTaylor\n",
          "date": "2025-11-07T17:02:00-05:00"
        },
        {
          "id": "email_wr_final_3@company.com",
          "from": "alex.smith@company.com",
          "to": [
            "taylor.brown@company.com"
          ],
          "subject": "Re: MOB – Weekly Update (week of Nov 7)",
          "body": "Thanks, Taylor.\n\nGlad the framing matches what you’re seeing. On Tuesday, I’d especially like to dig into the areas where performance work and new feature work intersect so we don’t accidentally regress any of these wins during the final push.\n\nAlex\n",
          "date": "2025-11-07T17:18:00-05:00"
        }
      ]
    }
  ]
}
